  "fdr_global_caption_en": "Table S7. Multiple-testing correction (Benjamini–Hochberg FDR at q = 0.05) over the global set of 588 ENSO tests (21 stations × 4 lags × 7 variables). Tests are Spearman rank correlations between monthly station-level time series of seven hydroclimatic variables (CHIRPS precipitation; ERA5-Land Tmean, Tmax, Tmin and relative humidity; TerraClimate ETP and PDSI) and the monthly Oceanic Niño Index (ONI). For each (variable, source, lag) cell we report the number of stations with raw p < 0.05 and the number retained after FDR-BH correction applied to the global set of 588 p-values. Reproducibility: scipy.stats.false_discovery_control(method='bh') applied to the P_VALOR column of the project file ENSO_VARIABLES_COMPLETAS.csv (Zenodo concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.19821757). Final outcome: 463 of 588 correlations remain significant after FDR-BH correction at q = 0.05 (raw count: 465/588). Detailed breakdown follows.",
